alternateNames: primary dysmenorrhea, menstrual cramps, menstrual pain, period pain, painful periods
description: Dysmenorrhea is the medical term for painful menstrual periods which are caused by uterine contractions. Primary dysmenorrhea refers to recurrent pain, while secondary dysmenorrhea results from reproductive system disorders. Both can be treated.
